      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:1:4:6:2",
      "text": [
        " لَوْ بَقِيَ اثْنَانِ لَكَانَ أَحَدُهُمَا الْحُجَّةَ عَلَى صَاحِبِهِ .",
        "مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ الْحَسَنِ عَنْ سَهْلِ بْنِ زِيَادٍ عَنْ مُحَمَّدِ بْنِ عِيسَى مِثْلَهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ahmad Bin Idrees and Muhammad Bin Yahya altogether, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Muhammad Bin Isa Bin Ubeyd, from Muhammad Bin Sinan, from Hamza Bin Al Tayyar, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘If two remain, it would be so that one of the two would be the Divine Authority upon his companion’. ",
          "<span style=\"font-size: small\">Muhammad Bin Al Hassan, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Muhammad Bin Isa</span> – similar to it."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          " 2. Ahmad ibn Idris and Muhammad ibn Yahya together have narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from Muhammad ibn ‘Isa from abu ‘Ubayd from Muhammad ibn Sinan from abu Hamza ibn al-Tayyar from abu ‘Abdallah (a.s.) who has said the following. “Would there remain only two people on earth, one of them would the person with divine authority over the other.” Muhammad ibn al-Hassan has narrated from Sahl ibn Ziyad from Muhammad ibn ‘Isa a similar Hadith."
        ]
      }
    },
